<subSubSection pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="89.[151,1437,1430,1745]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1430,1456]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species has a rugulose preepisternum, copper-red metasomal terga and striate gena and postgena, characteristics that separates it from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eickwort" authorityYear="1969" box="[636,813,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Oxystoglossella">
<emphasis box="[636,813,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Oxystoglossella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring at the southernmost South America. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lepeco &amp; Gonçalves, 2020" authorityName="Lepeco &amp; Gonçalves" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hestia" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Augochlora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">A. (Augochlora) hestia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[344,435,1503,1529]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[344,435,1503,1529]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to this species in color pattern, but lacks the typical characteristics of the subgenus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="89" pageNumber="90" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="89.[151,1437,1430,1745]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1574,1600]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1910" box="[344,567,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Augochlora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morrae">
<emphasis box="[344,567,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="90">Augochlora morrae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeco, A. &amp; Goncalves, R. B." box="[802,1125,1575,1601]" pageId="89" pageNumber="90" pagination="261 - 293" refId="ref75535" refString="Lepeco, A. &amp; Goncalves, R. B. (2020) New species of Augochlora (Oxystoglossella) Eickwort (Hymenoptera; Apoidea) from Northeastern Brazil with an identification key for the region. Zootaxa, 4802 (2), 261 - 293. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4802.2.3" type="journal article" year="2020">Lepeco &amp; Gonçalves (2020)</bibRefCitation>
, nests were studied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Michener, C. D. &amp; Lange, R. B." pageId="89" pageNumber="90" pagination="473 - 505" refId="ref75931" refString="Michener, C. D. &amp; Lange, R. B. (1958) Observations on the behavior of Brazilian Halictid bees, III. University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 39, 473 - 505." type="journal article" year="1958">Michener &amp; Lange (1958)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
